===2007 season===
{{see|2007 Kansas City Chiefs season}}
In the 2007 preseason, the Vikings hosted the Rams.<ref name="A Different Kind"/> Chiefs scout and vice president of player personnel [[Bill Kuharich]] attended the game at the [[Hubert H. Humphrey Metrodome]].<ref name="A Different Kind"/> Thigpen played in the fourth quarter and in two possessions with the Vikings offense and completed 3-of-6 passes for 29 yards and picked up 18 yards on two scrambles.<ref name="A Different Kind"/> Kuharich filed a scouting a report following the game and told the rest of the Chiefs personnel to keep an eye on Thigpen if he were to be released after the preseason.<ref name="A Different Kind"/>

On [[May 18]], [[2007]], Thigpen became the first of eight Vikings drafted in 2007 to sign a contract, agreeing to a four-year deal.<ref name="Tyler Thigpen biography"/><ref name="StarTrib"/> Thigpen then competed with [[Brooks Bollinger]], [[Tarvaris Jackson]], and [[Drew Henson]] for a quarterback roster spot for the [[2007 NFL season]].<ref name="StarTrib"/>  The Vikings released Thigpen on [[September 1]], [[2007]] thinking they could add him on their practice squad after passing waivers but he was signed by the Chiefs the following day.<ref name="Tyler Thigpen biography">{{cite web | title=Tyler Thigpen biography | url=http://www.kcchiefs.com/player/tyler_thigpen/ | publisher=Kansas City Chiefs | accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref>

Thigpen made his professional debut replacing an injured [[Damon Huard]] versus the [[San Diego Chargers]] on [[December 12]], [[2007]]. He finished the game 2-of-6 for 41 yards and an interception.<ref name="Chiefs have own">{{cite web | title=Chiefs have own QB problems as they play host to Oakland |url=http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/preview?game_id=29548&displayPage=tab_preview&season=2008&week=REG2 | author=Associated Press | publisher=NFL.com | date=2008-09-15 | accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref> He tore his [[medial collateral ligament]] (MCL) in practice that week and was placed on [[injured reserve]], ending his season.<ref name="Tyler Thigpen biography"/>

===2008 season===
{{see|2008 Kansas City Chiefs season}}
Prior to the 2008 season, Thigpen impressed Chiefs coaches enough to make the team think he could challenge for, and even win, the team's starting job against the incumbent [[Brodie Croyle]].<ref name="A Different Kind"/><ref name="unheralded">{{cite web | title=Chiefs, Panthers could turn to unheralded QBs | url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story?id=09000d5d8083036d&template=with-video&confirm=true | last=Schefter | first=Adam | publisher=NFL.com | date=2008-05-06 | accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref>
Thigpen was listed on the Chiefs' roster in [[2008 NFL season|2008]] and made his season debut on [[September 14]] against the [[Oakland Raiders]], when [[Damon Huard]] left with "mild head trauma."<ref name="replaced by Thigpen">{{cite web | title=Chiefs' Huard replaced by Thigpen after injury | author=Associated Press| url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3587431 | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-09-14 | accessdate=2008-09-14}}</ref><ref name="Despite firing">{{cite web | title=Despite firing reports, Kiffin, McFadden lead Raiders over Chiefs | url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=280914012 | author=Associated Press | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-09-14 | accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref> Thigpen connected on 14-of-33 passes for 151 yards.<ref name="Despite firing"/> Thigpen made his first NFL start on [[September 21]], [[2008]] against the [[Atlanta Falcons]].<ref name="Thigpen to start">{{cite web | title=Chiefs QB Thigpen to start vs. Falcons | author=Associated Press | url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3593861 | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-09-17 | accessdate=2008-09-17}}</ref> Thigpen struggled in the game, finishing 14-of-36 and passing for 128 yards with 3 interceptions in the 14&ndash;38 loss.<ref name="Turner scores">{{cite web | title=Turner scores three TDs as Falcons handle listless Chiefs | url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=280921001 | author=Associated Press | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-09-21 | accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref> The Chiefs trailed the Falcons 24&ndash;0 until Thigpen threw a touchdown pass to [[Dwayne Bowe]] just before halftime.<ref name="Turner scores"/> Thigpen's third interception was returned for a touchdown with just over a minute remaining the in the game.<ref name="Turner scores"/> In the week prior to the game, Chiefs coach [[Herman Edwards]] insisted he would substitute [[Damon Huard]] into the game if Thigpen struggled.<ref name="Turner scores"/> Edwards contemplated it during the game, but decided against it reasoning that Thigpen "put some points on the board."<ref name="Turner scores"/> Following the game, asked if Thigpen would keep the starting job, Edwards said, "We'll see."<ref name="Turner scores"/>

The following week, Huard was retained as the Chiefs' starting quarterback.<ref name="Huard will start">{{cite web | title=Huard will start at quarterback Sunday for Kansas City | url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story?id=09000d5d80b168a8&template=with-video&confirm=true | author=Associated Press | publisher=NFL.com | date=2008-09-22 | accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref> However, Thigpen was again awarded the starting position after Croyle and Huard were placed on injured reserve, ending both of their seasons.<ref name="Croyle sprains">{{cite web | author=Associated Press | title=Chiefs QB Croyle sprains right knee, done for the season  | publisher=ESPN.com | url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3652130 | date=2008-10-19 | accessdate=2008-10-19}}</ref><ref name="Breaking the Mold">{{cite web | title=Breaking the Mold | url=http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/11/13/breaking_the_mold/ | last=Rand | first=Jonathan | publisher=Kansas City Chiefs | date=2008-11-13 | accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref>

{{Quote box
 | quote  =I think you adjust to what your players do well... You start out with a system but the system has to be adjusted to the players you have. Tyler feels very comfortable in what he<U+2019>s doing and I think he has given us the best opportunity to move the ball, get first downs and score. We<U+2019>re rolling that way and we<U+2019>re not turning back.
 | source = <U+2014> [[Herman Edwards]] on implementing the [[spread offense]].<ref name="Spread changes"/><ref name="Breaking the Mold"/>
 | width  =33%
 | align  =left
}}

[[Image:081116Saints-Chiefs.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Thigpen (second from right) lines up with the Chiefs' offense in a [[shotgun formation]].]]
[[Image:081116Saints-Chiefs02.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Thigpen (first from left) lines up as a wide receiver on offense as RB Larry Johnson lines up as the quarterback in a [[wildcat formation]].]]
With the absence of running back [[Larry Johnson (American football)|Larry Johnson]], the central part of the Chiefs' offense in years past, offensive coordinator [[Chan Gailey]] adjusted the offense to mimic the spread formation run by Thigpen at Coastal Carolina.<ref name="Spread changes"/><ref name="Breaking the Mold"/> Herman Edwards and Chan Gailey chose to implement the spread in order to prepare Thigpen for his second career start.<ref name="Spread changes"/>

Head coach [[Herman Edwards]], who has long had a reputation for favoring more conservative, run-oriented offenses, began seeing his team gain confidence with every game it played in that wide-open system.<ref name="Spread changes">{{cite web | title=Spread changes options for Chiefs | url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/columns/story?id=3717080 | last=Chadiha | first=Jeffri | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-11-21 | accessdate=2008-11-26}}</ref> By implementing the spread offense, the Chiefs made a huge gamble, as most in the NFL believe that a [[spread offense]] cannot work in professional football.<ref name="Spread changes"/>

In Thigpen's second career start, he passed for 280 yards with a 69.4% completion rate, with two touchdowns and no interceptions against the [[New York Jets]], nearly leading the Chiefs to win over the heavily-favored Jets.<ref name="Favre connects">{{cite web | title=Favre connects with Coles in final minute to lift Jets to win | url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=281026020 | author=Associated Press | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-10-26 | accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref> With the newly installed spread offense, the Chiefs had four or five pass plays and two or three runs.<ref name="Spread changes"/>

Thigpen scored his first receiving touchdown the following week versus the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]].<ref name="Bucs overcome"/> The 37-yard pass was from wide receiver [[Mark Bradley]] in a [[Wildcat offense|Wildcat formation]].<ref name="Bucs overcome"/> Thigpen also passed for 164 yards, a touchdown, no interceptions, and a 56.0% completion rate in the 30&ndash;27 loss against the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]].<ref name="Bucs overcome"/> Thigpen became only the fifth player in Chiefs' history&ndash;and the first quarterback&ndash;to throw a touchdown pass and also score touchdowns by running and receiving.<ref name="Bucs overcome"/> In the game, the Chiefs led 24&ndash;3 with a little more than two minutes remaining in the second quarter and seemed headed for just their second victory of the season.<ref name="Bucs overcome">{{cite web | title=Bucs overcome four turnovers, 21-point deficit en route to OT win | url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=281102012 | author=Associated Press | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-11-02 | accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref> The Buccaneers rallied back and won the game in overtime with 24 unanswered points.<ref name="Bucs overcome"/>

[[Image:TylerThigpen110908.jpg|thumb|245px|left|Thigpen avoids a sack from [[Shaun Phillips]] in a game against the San Diego Chargers.]]Thigpen continued his impressive play the following week in the Chiefs' 20&ndash;19 loss to the [[San Diego Chargers]], completing 27-of-41 passes for 266 yards, three touchdowns and no interceptions.<ref name="Chiefs' 2-point">{{cite web | title=Chiefs' 2-point conversion falls short as Chargers avoid upset | url=http://scores.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=281109024 | author=Associated Press | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-11-09 | accessdate=2008-12-04}}</ref> That gave him six touchdown passes and no turnovers in his previous three games.<ref name="Chiefs' 2-point"/>

After throwing three interceptions against the Falcons and appearing lucky to avoid throwing twice that many, Thigpen competed 124 straight passes without an interception through Week 10.<ref name="Breaking the Mold"/> Thigpen's no-interception streak ended at 161 in the closing seconds of a 30&ndash;20 loss to the [[New Orleans Saints]], but Thigpen still managed to complete 19-of-38 passes for 235 yards and two touchdowns to [[Dwayne Bowe]].<ref name="Brees throws">{{cite web | title=Brees throws for 266 yards and TD to help Saints win in Kansas City | url=http://scores.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=281116012 | author=Associated Press | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-11-16 | accessdate=2008-12-04}}</ref> Thigpen became the first Chiefs quarterback to throw a touchdown pass in four consecutive games since [[Trent Green]] in 2005.<ref name="Brees throws"/>

Prior to the Chiefs implementing the spread offense, Thigpen had been playing erratically with the Chiefs, and he suddenly became poised and effective running the new offense.<ref name="A copycat game">{{cite web | title=A copycat game | url=http://www.kcchiefs.com/news/2008/12/02/a_copycat_game/ | last=Rand | first=Jonathan | publisher=Kansas City Chiefs | date=2008-12-02 | accessdate=2008-12-03}}</ref> His passer rating has climbed from 44.3 to 76.9 in the five games following his initial start at Atlanta.<ref name="A copycat game"/> The Chiefs scored more than 10 points just twice in their first six games.<ref name="A copycat game"/> They<U+2019>ve scored more offensive points than that in every game since, and twice have topped 25.<ref name="A copycat game"/>

Thigpen had his first bad game in five outings against the [[Buffalo Bills]] on [[November 23]] in the Chiefs' 54&ndash;31 loss.<ref name="Edwards helps Bills">{{cite web | title=Edwards helps Bills score most against Chiefs in history | url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=281123012 | author=Associated Press | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-11-23 | date=2008-11-23}}</ref> Thigpen's three turnovers (two interceptions and one lost fumble) led to 20 points by the Bills.<ref name="Edwards helps Bills"/> Despite the turnovers, Thigpen also threw for 240 yards and three touchdowns.<ref name="Edwards helps Bills"/>

Thigpen won his first game as the Chiefs' starter on November 30 against the Oakland Raiders, leading Kansas City to a 20&ndash;13 victory.<ref name="Johnson's 2-yard">{{cite web | title=Johnson's 2-yard plunge lifts Chiefs over woeful Raiders | url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=281130013 | author=Associated Press | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-11-30 | accessdate=2008-12-01}}</ref> Thigpen finished 15-of-22 for 162 yards and ran for 48 more.<ref name="Johnson's 2-yard"/> The victory ended a 7-game losing streak for the Chiefs.<ref name="Johnson's 2-yard"/> The following week, Thigpen kept the Chiefs competitive against the [[Denver Broncos]], holding onto a 17&ndash;17 tie into the fourth quarter.<ref name="Broncos get">{{cite web | title=Broncos get it together in 4th, put end to 3-game home skid | url=http://scores.espn.go.com/nfl/recap?gameId=281207007 | author=Associated Press | publisher=ESPN.com | date=2008-12-07 | accessdate=2008-12-08}}</ref> After the Chiefs lost the lead to Denver, Thigpen drove the Chiefs all the way to the Broncos' 5-yard line, where his draw on fourth-and-goal was snuffed out by Broncos cornerback [[Dr<U+00E9> Bly]] at the 1-yard line.<ref name="Broncos get"/> The Broncos held their 24&ndash;17 lead and sent the Chiefs to a 2-11 record on the season.<ref name="Broncos get"/>

